This is a document for installing Ovirt 4.4 on CentOs 8.3 as a self-hosted engine.

Explain what is Ovirt (its definition here) and what is a self hosted engine. Then mentioned some of the pre-req such as DNS.

1=> Install CentOs 8.3 and update.
2=> Install the Ovirt official Repo:
    $ dnf install https://resources.ovirt.org/pub/yum-repo/ovirt-release44.rpm -y
    $ dnf update -y
3=> Enable Javapackage tool
    $ dnf module enable -y javapackages-tools pki-deps postgresql:12 389-ds
    
4=> Install the ovirt-engine:
    $ dnf install ovirt-engine -y && engine-setup
    
 Follow the prompt and complete the install, I have mainly chose a lot of the defautl config but find below my answer file:
    # OTOPI answer file, generated by human dialog
[environment:default]
QUESTION/1/GRAFANA_USE_ENGINE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=str:yes
